            <br />
           <h3> Text editor for writing Html Code</h3>
           <br />
           <br />
           <p> We can use any text editor for writing HTML code. For example, we can use Notepad, visual studio, visual studio code, dreamweaver,sublime or any other text editor.</p>
           <p>Html file has the file extension of .html. for example if we want to save an html file as book in notepad, then save the file as book.html</p>
           <h3>OTHER HTML elements or TAGS</h3>
           <div class="bg-success">
           <h5 >Heading Tags</h5>
           <p>1.&lt;h1&gt;&lt;/h1&gt; This is the biggest heading tag among other heading tags. As i said earlier html is not case sensitive. so we can write h1 start and closing tags as &lt;H1&gt;&lt;/H1&gt; also
           <p>2.&lt;h2&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;</p>
           <p>3.&lt;h3&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;</p>
           <p>3.&lt;h4&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;</p>
           <p>3.&lt;h5&gt;&lt;/h5&gt;</p>
            </div>
            <h3>Paragraph tag</h3>
            <p>&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt; denotes the paragraph tag</p>
            <h3>Division tag</h3>
            <p>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt; denotes the Division tag</p>
             <h3>Marquee tag</h3>
            <p>Marguee tag is used for scrolling the text &lt;marquee&gt;&lt;/marquee&gt; we can also set its direction to vertical or horizontal</p>
           <h3>HTML Comment Tag</h3>
           <p>Html comment tag is used to write something inside program as a note, but it won't be compiled or executed as a part of program</p>
           <p>&lt;!-- Write comments here --&gt;</p>
